- cocos2d-x version: 3.14.1
- devices test on: Mac
 I have ui::ListView with 8 items. I add event listeners to button to loop through the items. 
```
void PanelSeed::onBtnNextAction()
{
    if(selectedIndex != listView->getItems().size() - 1)
    {
        ++selectedIndex;
        listView->scrollToItem(selectedIndex, Vec2(0, 0), Vec2(0, 0));
    }
}
```
Clipping part of ui::ListView 4 items. When I loop under 5 element i got glitch with position of  inner container, because his position move under the boundary and return to maximal position without animation. I think the problem is in function:
```
void ScrollView::startAutoScrollToDestination(const Vec2& destination, float timeInSec, bool attenuated)
{
    startAutoScroll(destination - _innerContainer->getPosition(), timeInSec, attenuated);
}
```
On my project I must fix this problem, I have 2 ways: add workaround in my code or fix it in engine. 
Can I fix it in engine and add code of fix to this issue? Or better create workaround?
P. S.
  Also, I need inner margin for ui::ListView. If I add it to ui::ListView is it be good? I know it old [problem](http://discuss.cocos2d-x.org/t/listview-container-margins/21081), and nobody fix it. 
Can I fix it in engine?

